folder: Rodney Street & Bedford Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Rodney Street, south side, at and east of Bedford Ave., showing at the corner the Oscar Hawley Mansion, purchased by the Hanover Club in 1891 for $27,000 and enlarged. In 1922, a Jewish Society known as the "Young Israel of Williamsburg" purchased the club for $35,000.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
